<TITLE> Matin takes credit for Khaleda-Hasina talks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 23 (bdnews24.com)  Home adviser M A Matin has taken the credit for arranging the face-to-face meeting between former prime ministers Sheikh Hasina and Khaleda Zia on Thursday. He said during the programme to mark the Armed Forces Day at Sena Kunja in Dhaka Cantonment, he spotted both leaders and re-directed their routes so that they would come face to face. "I consider myself fortunate for being able to arrange the meeting between the two leaders," he said. "The nation waited for two long years to see such a moment," he said after a meeting at the home ministry on the law and order situation ahead of the upcoming Upazila election. Referring to the conversation, he said Hasina, upon seeing Khaleda, exchanged pleasantries and said during their time in jail she had sent cooked food to Khaleda which the latter acknowledged. b
